d with wife Mary Corse Lyman."},"education":[{"school_name":"McGill College, Montreal","type":"undergraduate","notes":"Graduated McGill College, Montreal — per EH bio. McGill founded 1821 in Montreal; Henry would have attended in the 1830s."},{"school_name":"College in England (unnamed)","type":"graduate","notes":"Further study at a college in England per EH bio — specific institution undocumented."},{"school_name":"Bar of the Province of Quebec","type":"law","notes":"Admitted to practice law in the Province of Quebec."}],"career":[{"role":"Drug merchant, partner","organization":"Lyman Brothers (Lyman Bros & Co.), Montreal","location":"Montreal, Quebec, Canada","start_year":1829,"notes":"Joined the family drug firm in 1829 at age 15-16. Partner in Lyman Brothers — the largest pharmaceutical wholesaler in Canada — alongside his older brothers William and Benjamin. Listed as Drug Merchant in St Antoine Ward Montreal in the 1881 census."},{"role":"Lawyer, partner","organization":"Lyman, Class & Co. (law firm)","location":"Montreal, Quebec, Canada","notes":"Admitted to practice law in the Province of Quebec; partner in Lyman, Class & Co. law firm. Distinct from Lyman Brothers drug firm."},{"role":"Superintendent of West Ward","organization":"Montreal City Council","location":"Montreal","notes":"Served on Montreal City Council as Superintendent of West Ward."},{"role":"Deacon","organization":"Congregational Church, Montreal","location":"Montreal"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"McGill graduate, Quebec lawyer, Lyman Brothers partner","body":"Henry Lyman graduated McGill College Montreal and studied further in England before being admitted to practice law in the Province of Quebec. He joined the family drug firm in 1829 at age fifteen and became a partner in Lyman Brothers — the largest pharmaceutical wholesaler in Canada — while also serving on Montreal City Council as Superintendent of West Ward and as Deacon in the Congregational Church."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Three sons died young, four to old age","body":"Henry and Mary Corse Lyman had seven children together in Montreal between 1844 and 1861. Three died young: Arthur Ellis as an infant in 1847, Susan Alice at age five in 1853, and Roswell Corse at forty-two in 1892. The four surviving sons lived long lives, including Henry Herbert (who perished on the Empress of Ireland 1914) and Walter Ernest who reached eighty-nine."}],"slug":"henry-lyman-1813"},"X01252":{"id":"X01252","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":["canada_migration"],"sources":[],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD0583","date_year":1841,"date_month":8,"date_day":24,"location_city":"Montréal","location_state":"Quebec","location_country":"Canada","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1897,"children_ids":["HD4178","HD4179","HD4180","HD4181","HD0587","HD0588","HD4182"]}],"parents":{"father_research_notes":"Surname Corse; family of Northfield Franklin Co MA. Not built per Jalapeño Rule."},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1823,"month":10,"day":17,"city":"Northfield","county":"Franklin County","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1908,"month":11,"day":30,"city":"Montréal","state":"Quebec","country":"Canada"},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Mary Corse Lyman","first_name":"Mary","last_name":"Lyman","maiden_name":"Corse","married_names":[],"gender":"female","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1778699549/marylyman-resized_c1xavi.jpg","photo_notes":"Portrait of Mary Corse Lyman (1823-1908), wife of Henry Lyman."},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM328","plot_notes":"Cimetière Mont-Royal Montreal — buried with husband Henry Lyman."},"slug":"mary-corse-1823"},"X01250":{"id":"X01250","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":["canada_migration","vermont_migration","new_york_migration"],"sources":[],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00463","date_year":1793,"date_month":1,"date_day":10,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1814,"children_ids":["HD0580","HD4172","HD4173","HD0581","HD4174","HD4175","HD4176","HD4177","HD0582","HD0583"]}],"parents":{"father_name":"Elisha Lyman","mother_name":"Abigail Janes Lyman","father_research_notes":"Of Northampton MA. Elisha Sr. left his son Elisha Jr. the family homestead; Elisha Jr. exchanged it with his brother Theodore and left Northampton.","mother_research_notes":"Of Northampton MA, maiden name Janes."},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1770,"month":1,"day":26,"city":"Northampton","county":"Hampshire County","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1844,"month":2,"day":21,"city":"Champlain","county":"Clinton County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Elisha Lyman Jr.","first_name":"Elisha","last_name":"Lyman","married_names":[],"suffix":"Jr.","gender":"male"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM328","plot_notes":"Cimetière Mont-Royal, Outremont Montréal — per FA #251558309. Family memorial commemorates Elisha together with all three of his wives."},"career":[{"role":"Farmer","organization":"Various — Northampton/Conway/Derby/Montreal/Sunderland/Champlain","notes":"Per EH bio: farmer who settled successively at Conway MA, Derby VT, Montreal (where he resided from 1815 to 1828, thirteen years), Sunderland MA, and Champlain NY. Inherited the family homestead from his father Elisha Sr. but exchanged it with his brother Theodore and left Northampton."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Six-state migration across forty years, three wives","body":"Elisha Lyman Jr. married three times — Hannah Stiles in 1793 (died 1814), Thankful Hunt the same year Hannah died, and Sarah Beaumont in 1837 the same year Thankful died. He moved his family across an extraordinary geographic arc: Northampton Massachusetts to Conway Massachusetts, then Derby Vermont, then thirteen years in Montreal Canada from 1815 to 1828, then Sunderland Massachusetts, finally Champlain New York where he died in 1844 at age seventy-four."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Memorialized with all three wives in Montreal","body":"Elisha Lyman Jr. died at Champlain New York February 21, 1844 at age seventy-four. He was buried at Cimetière Mont-Royal in Montreal — the city where his second wife Thankful had died in 1837, and where his sons William, Benjamin, and Henry had settled to build the Lyman Brothers drug empire. A family memorial at Mount Royal commemorates Elisha together with all three of his wives."}],"slug":"elisha-lyman-jr-1770"},"H00463":{"id":"H00463","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1768,"month":5,"day":16,"city":"Windsor","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1814,"month":2,"day":25,"city":"Derby","state":"Vermont"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM327","plot_notes":"Derby Center Cemetery, Orleans County Vermont — per FindAGrave #235170328. Died a year before husband Elisha relocated the surviving family to Montreal."},"parents":{"father_id":"H00241","mother_id":"I00160"},"marriages":[{"children_ids":["HD0580","HD4172","HD4173","HD0581","HD4174","HD4175","HD4176","HD4177","HD0582","HD0583"],"spouse_id":"X01250","marriage_number":1}],"tags":["not_yet_fully_entered","canada_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 463"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Hannah Stiles Lyman","first_name":"Hannah","last_name":"Lyman","married_names":["Lyman"],"maiden_name":"Stiles"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Died at forty-five, before family's Montreal move","body":"Hannah Stiles Lyman died February 25, 1814 at Derby Vermont, age forty-five — one year before her widower Elisha relocated the surviving family to Montreal where they would remain for thirteen years. She had borne ten children over twenty years; two had died in infancy (Ashbel Stiles in 1796 and Horace in 1798) and the youngest, Henry, was only four months old when she died. Her three eldest surviving sons would become the founders of Lyman Brothers, the largest pharmaceutical wholesaler in Canada."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Mother of the Lyman drug dynasty","body":"Three of Hannah Stiles Lyman's sons — William (Montreal druggist), Benjamin (co-founder of Lyman Brothers, the largest pharmaceutical company in Canada), and Henry (Montreal lawyer and Lyman Brothers partner) — together built the Lyman drug empire across Montreal and Toronto. Her grandson Henry Herbert Lyman would later bequeath his entomology collection to McGill University, founding what became the Lyman Entomological Museum."}],"slug":"hannah-lyman-1768"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM328","name":"Cimetière Mont-Royal","city":"Outremont","state":"Montréal Region","country":"Canada","founded":1852,"wikipedia_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Royal_Cemetery","primary_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/639448/cimeti%C3%A8re-mont-royal","hooker_connections":["HD0580","HD0583","HD0584","HD0585","HD0586","HD0587","HD0588","HD4178","HD4182","HD4183","HD4187","HD4188","HD4189","HD4190","HD4191","HD4192","HD4194","HD4196","HD4198","HD4199","HD4210","HD4211","HD4213","HD4214","HD4219","HD4220","HD4221","HD4228","HD4229","I00630","I00631","I00632","I00634","I00640","I00641","I00643","I00645","I00646","I00647","X01250","X01251","X01252","X01253","X01591","X02825","I01230"],"notes":"Cimetière Mont-Royal (Mount Royal Cemetery), Outremont, Montreal QC. Major Protestant cemetery founded 1852 on the slopes of Mount Royal. Burial site of multiple members of the Lyman family — Hannah Stiles Lyman's descendants who became prominent Montreal druggists, lawyers, and civic figures: Elisha Lyman Jr. (with his three wives memorialized together), Henry Lyman, Mary Corse Lyman, Henry Herbert Lyman (later commemorated here after death on the Empress of Ireland 1914), Albert Clarence Lyman, Frederick Stiles Lyman, Edith Mary Louise Lyman, and others."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}